sql:
SELECT f.film_title
FROM films f
WHERE f.worldwide_gross > (
    SELECT MIN(fr.revenue)
    FROM financial_reports fr
    JOIN films f2 ON fr.film_id = f2.film_id
    WHERE f2.worldwide_gross = (
        SELECT MIN(worldwide_gross) FROM films
    )
);

external_knowledge:
- 'Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures' is a well-known distributor of films, often associated with high-grossing blockbusters.;
- 'Domestic sales' refer to box office earnings within the originating country, typically the United States. 'Worldwide gross' includes all earnings from screenings in all countries worldwide.;
- The metaphorical expression 'soared the highest domestically' refers to achieving the highest domestic sales, while 'the treasure it has gathered globally' refers to the worldwide gross.

sql:
SELECT record_date, domestic_sales, foreign_sales, total_sales, theater_count, average_ticket_price, weekend_gross
FROM box_office_records
WHERE film_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT film_id
FROM financial_reports
WHERE profit < 0;

SELECT AVG(CAST(budget AS INTEGER)) AS average_budget
FROM films
WHERE released_year >= 2010 AND CAST(budget AS INTEGER) > 0;

external_knowledge:
- Successful films refer to those with a worldwide gross over $50 million;
- Turn of the millennium refers to films released between the years 2000 and 2010;
- "Big bucks" implies significant financial success, typically associated with high box office grosses.
